@startuml
title IntentSpecification consumer-submitted profile proposal

skinparam shadowing false
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
skinparam ArrowColor #424242
skinparam RectangleBorderColor #424242

rectangle "TMF921 IntentSpecification\nbase resource model" as TMF #EEF2FF

rectangle "ID MS proposed consumer profile\n\nTMF-aligned, not TMF-minimal" as PROFILE #E8F5E9

TMF --> PROFILE : proposed stricter profile\nfor ID MS consumers


rectangle "Attribute classification

TMF-aligned base attributes
- name
- description
- isBundle
- validFor
- relatedParty
- specCharacteristic
- expressionSpecification
- targetEntitySchema
- @type, @baseType, @schemaLocation

ID MS extended attributes
- specKey
- intentBehaviour
- intentLayer
- schemaHash where governed" as EXT_ATTR #F3E5F5

PROFILE --> EXT_ATTR : calls out base and
extended attributes

rectangle "Consumer-submitted DRAFT create profile" as DRAFT_CREATE #FFF8E1 {
  rectangle "Minimum mandatory\n\n- specKey\n- name\n- @type\n- @baseType" as DRAFT_MIN
  rectangle "Strongly recommended\n\n- description\n- isBundle\n- validFor.startDateTime\n- relatedParty\n- specCharacteristic\n- expressionSpecification\n- targetEntitySchema" as DRAFT_REC
  rectangle "Optional classification\n\n- intentBehaviour\n- intentLayer\n\nClassification only.\nNot used by ID MS for runtime\ndecisioning, validation, admission\ncontrol, or behavioural enforcement." as DRAFT_OPT
}

rectangle "Server-managed identity\nand version fields" as SERVER #E3F2FD {
  rectangle "Consumer must not send\nin POST request\n\n- id\n- href\n- draftId\n- official version\n- lifecycleStatus\n- timestamps\n- _links\n- ETag\n- Location" as PROHIBITED
  rectangle "ID MS assigns\n\nspecKey = consumer-submitted logical key\nid = server-assigned official lineage key\ndraftId = server-assigned DRAFT candidate key\nversion = server-assigned on ACTIVE publication" as SERVER_ASSIGN
}

rectangle "New version handling" as VERSIONING #E0F2F1 {
  rectangle "Consumer submits same specKey\nfor a new version of an existing specification" as SAME_KEY
  rectangle "ID MS resolution rule\n\nExisting ACTIVE lineage for specKey:\nattach new DRAFT candidate to existing id\n\nNo ACTIVE lineage:\ncreate new server-generated id\n\nOnly RETIRED versions:\ncreate new id by default unless\ngovernance allows lineage reuse" as ID_RESOLUTION
}

rectangle "Consumer-submitted ACTIVE publication profile" as ACTIVE_PROFILE #FFECB3 {
  rectangle "Minimum mandatory before ACTIVE\n\n- name\n- @type\n- @baseType\n- validFor.startDateTime\n- expressionSpecification\n- expressionSpecification.iri\n- expressionSpecification.expressionLanguage\n- targetEntitySchema\n- specCharacteristic" as ACTIVE_MIN
  rectangle "Strongly recommended\n\n- description\n- isBundle\n- relatedParty\n- schemaHash where available\n- intentBehaviour\n- intentLayer" as ACTIVE_REC
  rectangle "Optional\n\n- validFor.endDateTime\n- additional relatedParty entries\n- schema metadata\n- lifecycle-aware _links in responses" as ACTIVE_OPT
}

rectangle "Out of scope for this proposal" as OUT #FFEBEE {
  rectangle "Operation routing\nActivation mechanics\nRetire behaviour\nHub subscriptions\nRuntime Intent admission\nDraftId provenance lookup" as OUT_ITEMS
}

PROFILE --> DRAFT_CREATE : defines what consumers send\nfor DRAFT creation
DRAFT_CREATE --> SERVER : server fills identity,\nstate, and response metadata
DRAFT_CREATE --> VERSIONING : specKey supports\nnew version authoring
PROFILE --> ACTIVE_PROFILE : defines what must be supplied\nbefore ACTIVE publication
PROFILE -[#gray,dashed]-> OUT : intentionally excluded

note bottom of DRAFT_OPT
intentBehaviour fields:
category, constraintMode, objectiveType, fulfilmentMode

intentLayer values:
BUSINESS, SERVICE, RESOURCE
end note

note bottom of ACTIVE_PROFILE
CONTINUOUS fulfilmentMode indicates downstream systems
may operate in a closed-loop manner to maintain the
intent objective over time. It does not imply mutation
of the submitted runtime Intent instance.
end note

note right of EXT_ATTR
Extended attributes are part of the ID MS
profile proposal, not TMF-native fields.
They support governance, authoring,
classification, and schema integrity only.
They do not add runtime fulfilment logic
to ID MS.
end note

@enduml
